<html>
	<head>
		<link rel="stylesheet" href="https://stackpath.bootstrapcdn.com/bootstrap/4.3.1/css/bootstrap.min.css" integrity="sha384-ggOyR0iXCbMQv3Xipma34MD+dH/1fQ784/j6cY/iJTQUOhcWr7x9JvoRxT2MZw1T" crossorigin="anonymous">
		<script type="text/javascript">
		function checkval(form){
			if(form.val1.value<1 || form.val2.value<1 || form.val31.value<1 || form.val32.value<1 || form.val4.value<1 || form.val5.value<1)
				{
					alert("Please fill all the entries")
					return false
				}
			else{
				return true
			}
		}
	</script>
		<style>
#customers {
  font-family: "Trebuchet MS", Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;
  border-collapse: collapse;
  width: 100%;
}

#customers td, #customers th {
  border: 1px solid #ddd;
  padding: 8px;
}

#customers tr:nth-child(even){background-color: #f2f2f2;}

#customers tr:hover {background-color: #ddd;}

#big{
	font-size: 150%;
}
			
#customers th {
  padding-top: 12px;
  padding-bottom: 12px;
  text-align: left;
  background-color: blue;
  color: white;
}
</style>
	</head>
<h2 align="center">
	EVALUATION RUBRIC: <b>Doctoral Thesis Defense (Abstract)</b>
</h2>
<div class="container">
  <div class="row">
    <div class="col-sm">
		<b>Student ID:</b> <%= stuid %>
    </div>
    <div class="col-sm">
		<b>Evaluator:</b> <%= ename %>
    </div>
    <div class="col-sm">
		<b>Abstract Date Of Evaluation:</b> <%= dates %>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
<form action="/success/<%= stuid %>/<%= ename %>/<%= dates %>/<%= formtype %>" method="POST" onSubmit=" return checkval(this)">
<div class="container">
	<table id="customers">
  <tr>
    <th id="big">Evaluation</th>
    <th>Unacceptable</th>
    <th>Marginal</th>
	<th>Acceptable</th>
  </tr>
  <tr>
	  <td><b>1. Achievement of Aim and Objectives:</b>
Stated solution clearly for the research problem; 
Strategic breakdown of solution through objective is
		  quantified and achievement is effective</td>
    <td><input type="radio" name="val1" value="1">Objectives and thereby aim is
incomplete or unmet</td>
    <td><input type="radio" name="val1" value="2">Aim and Objectives are achieved
but partially quantifiable in terms
of outcomes</td>
	  <td><input type="radio" name="val1" value="3">Aim and Objectively are clearly
achieved and outcomes are
also quantified in respective of
them</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
	  <td><b>2. Stability in Methodology:</b>
Sound state‐of‐the-art research methodology to solve;
Used modern methods and tools associated in
developing solution.</td>
    <td><input type="radio" name="val2" value="1">Methodology is lacking usage of
out-of-box techniques for more
and effective solution</td>
    <td><input type="radio" name="val2" value="2">Methodology is partially effective
and has adapted from existing
with very limited changes</td>
	  <td><input type="radio" name="val2" value="3">Stability in the methodology is
reflected with a definite state
of art and has used very
recent advancements to
conduct </td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
	  <td><b>3. Novelty and Contribution – Research Impact:</b><br><br>
Demonstrated potential value of solution through
contribution to the research problem in advancing
knowledge within and outside the area/field of study.<br>
Demonstrated awareness of broad implications or
research; Broader impacts may include societal,
economic, technical, ethical, technological or business
aspects</td>
    <td><input type="radio" name="val31" value="1">No Significant novelty and contribution reflected. Solution provided
is obsolete, hence not very valued
within or outside the field of study<br><br>
	  <input type="radio" name="val32" value="1">Limited to theoritical, no commercial aspect</td>
    <td><input type="radio" name="val31" value="2">Demonstrated a decent
contribution, however lacks novelty to make a greater impact to the field of study<br><br>
		<input type="radio" name="val32" value="2">Research is having a commercial
angle however, not explored</td>
	  <td><input type="radio" name="val31" value="3">Demonstrated valid novelty and made potential contribution to fundamental / conceptul knowledge in areas of study<br><br><input type="radio" name="val32" value="3">Commercial aspect addressed
through patent publication </td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
	  <td><b>4. Validation of Results and Evaluation:</b>
Demonstrated sound knowledge in the area,
Prior literature on specific research problem.
Analyzed and interpreted Research data effectively.</td>
    <td><input type="radio" name="val4" value="1">Results obtained are not
substantial enough to validate the
achievement of aim. Poor
evaluation shown</td>
    <td><input type="radio" name="val4" value="2">Demonstrated relevant results to
achieve aim and objectives,
reflected the quality of results</td>
	  <td><input type="radio" name="val4" value="3"> Extensive and critical results that
demonstrate achievement of
aim and contribution.
Reflected the quality of results</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
	  <td><b>5. Quality of Written and Oral Skills:</b>
Research Thesis (a) written and (b) Defense</td>
    <td><input type="radio" name="val5" value="1">Poor written and oral communication</td>
    <td><input type="radio" name="val5" value="2">Marginal written and oral skills, seeds improvement</td>
	  <td><input type="radio" name="val5" value="3">Publication quality written and oral skills</td>
  </tr>
</table>
	<br>
	<h5>
		Comments
	</h5>
	<textarea rows="4" cols="156" name="comment"></textarea>
	<button type="submit" class="btn btn-primary">Submit</button>
	</div>
	</form>
</html>